{
  "texts": [
    "According to Liu (2012), SA is a field of study in which computers analyze people's expressions of opinions, emotions, and attitudes in text.",
    "It is an interesting problem with significant implications for both business and society.",
    "ABSA is a sub-task of SA that focuses on aspect-level sentiment analysis, identifying the following elements (ACOS) in each sentence.",
    "These four sentiment elements constitute the core of ABSA research.",
    "ACOSQE aims to extract all aspect-category-opinion-sentiment polarity quadruples from the text to more comprehensively and accurately reflect sentiment information."
  ]
}